	(text "The capacitance between op amps is critical.\nIf it gets to 100f the system collapses."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 138.43 135.89 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "00db79eb-37e8-47da-940f-84b0156aede2")
	)
	(text "Oddly enough, if the parasitic capacitance is too low, it becomes \nunstable.\nKeep an eye on the phase margin (the phase distance to -180 at 0db \ngain should be greater than 45).\nBeyond that, a cutoff frequency to high adds unecessary high \nfrequency noise."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 30.48 127.762 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "2d848fcb-2707-49bf-84a4-f55c068829ac")
	)
	(text "The range texts ARE NOT guarantees.\nThey only show ranges I got working on simulation after tweaking multiple values to work together."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 81.026 52.07 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "36bc7128-9fb5-4e99-a4cd-81e93a5b7a5d")
	)
	(text "0 to 100p"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 79.502 111.506 0)
		(effects
